Installation Requisites
***********************

Fall3d is written in Fortran 90 and links the external library netCDF.
It was tested un UNIX/Linux platforms including MacOS.

Fall can be compiled for running in serial mode (one processor) and
parallel mode (multiple processor and/or clusters based on MPI).

For compiling the serial version you need:

 *) Fortran 90 compiler (eg: ifort,gfortran, xlf90, etc.)
 *) Library netCDF installed on your machine (versions 3.6.*, 4.* or later).
    NETCDF library is available from: http://www.unidata.ucar.edu/netcdf/


In addition, for compiling the parallel version (optional), you need

 *) MPI or OpenMPI installed on you machine with Fortran compilation
    enabled (command mpif90 available).


Installation Instructions
*************************

Sources of Fall3d-7.0 are distributed as gzipped tar archive in a
file named fall3d-7.0.tar.gz available at the following URLs:

  http://www.bsc.es/projects/earthscience/fall3d/
  http://datasim.ov.ingv.it/Fall3d.html

After you obtained file fall3d-7.0.tar.gz, copy it in a directory and unpack
the tarball with the command:

    $ tar zxvf fall3d-7.0.tar.gz

This creates the directory fall3d-7.0 containing all the Fall3d sources,
scripts and the manual.

For more information refer to the pdf version of the manual
(file fall3d-7.0.pdf), located in the directory fall3d-7.0/Manual
